§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $(Ω, ℱ, 𝗣)$ is a probability space and $x: Ω →
    𝗥^n$ is a random vector. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬covariance matrix❭ of $x$ is the matrix $A ∈ 𝗥^{n ×
    n}$ defined by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ A_{ij} = \cov(x_i, x_j) \quad \text{for all } i, j =
        1, …, n ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉
